-- Piaggio Plans to Make $3,400 Car in India in 3 Years, Business Line Says
-- B y   A d i   N a r a y a n
-- 2010-11-04T02:05:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/piaggio-plans-to-make-3-400-car-in-india-in-3-years-business-line-says.html
Piaggio & C. SpA, the Italian maker
of Vespa scooters, plans to introduce a 150,000 rupee ($3,400)
small car in India in the next three years, the Business Line
reported, citing Ravi Chopra, the head of Piaggio’s Indian unit.  The prototype was displayed at the Milan Bike show, and it
will be manufactured at the company’s plant near Pune in western
India, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
